defaultBridget Andersondefault: There is a very fundamental problem with what constitutes slavery, given that we are not talking about chattel slavery, given that it is not about a slave system, and, given that the more constrained one’s options, the more enthusiastically one will consent to abysmal conditions. You are not going to find me working for 
defaulttuppence
default 
